                              INSTALLATION GUIDE

NOTE: all steps do using application owner user (for example:
      @ARCHIVES_BASE_NAME@).

  $ sudo su -- @ARCHIVES_BASE_NAME@

NOTE: please, skip previous step if you are using same user for application
      run

1. unpack application distribution archive into some folder:

  $ unzip /path/to/@ARCHIVES_BASE_NAME@-@VERSION@.zip -d /tmp/

2. change directory inside unpacked folder where application.yaml file is
   locating:

  $ cd /tmp/@ARCHIVES_BASE_NAME@

3. update application configuration file application.yaml if needed:

  $ vi ./application.yaml

4. run application:

  $ bash ./@ARCHIVES_BASE_NAME@-@VERSION@.jar
